Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).
Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%grams}. Fry, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%grams}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain and pop back in the pan. Cover.

Drain and discard any excess fat from the beef. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Add the @Caribbean Style Jerk{2%sachets} and @Dried Thyme{1%sachet}.

Stir through the @Tomato Puree{30%grams}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{150%milliliter}s.

Simmer, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Next, add the @Baby Spinach{40%grams} in handfuls so it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Stir in the @BBQ Sauce{48%grams} and @Butter{20%grams}. Add a splash of water if needed.

Share the rice and beef mince between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @Chilli Flakes{1%pinch} to finish.

Enjoy!